Dar es Salaam. Central Bank (BoT) Benno Ndulu says in Dar es Salaam Wednesday that Tanzania's economic growth is on track and there is no reason to worry. BoT governor Benno Ndulu dismisses critics saying they are wrong to use statistics of only one quarter of the year to assess economic growth.Bank of Tanzania governor Benno Ndulu says there is a re-distribution of money in the economy from the pockets of corrupt people to budgetary activities due to improved revenue collection, austerity measures and anti-corruption efforts.He says similar concerns on the economy and money circulation existed even during the third phase government when President Benjamin Mkapa launched an anti-corruption drive. It was then called 'Ukapa'. 